{
  "texts": [
    "After collecting features from the hybrid ResNet50 and YOLOv5 model, the XGBoost classifier is used to categorize brain tumor grades, which is an efficient method for precise and trustworthy tumor grading.",
    "Our model, which was a customized integration of modified YOLOv5 backbone and a ResNet50, was optimized and fine-tuned in terms of the number of parameters.",
    "Consequently, a model configuration with approximately 28.16 million parameters was produced.On a machine with the NVIDIA GeForce GTX and Intel(R) Core (TM) i7/4.5 GHz specifications, the model's processing time was measured.",
    "An image's processing takes about 30 milliseconds on average.",
    "We compare the suggested hybrid model to various approaches that have been investigated in the literature that use the WSI from the TCGA."
  ]
}